(44, 17, 24, 40, 11, 25, 25, 'Lord of heaven and earth', 'Connection of Lordship and Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize God as ''Lord of heaven and earth.'' This connection highlights the divine authority of God and His role in revealing truth to the humble.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 24, 19, 115, 16, 16, 'Lord of heaven and earth', 'Divine Sovereignty Over Creation', 'This connection highlights God''s sovereignty over both heaven and earth. Acts 17:24 emphasizes that God is the Lord of heaven and earth, while Psalms 115:16 notes that the earth is given to humanity, indicating a divine order in creation.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 25, 19, 50, 8, 13, 'he giveth to all life, and breath, and all things', 'Divine Sufficiency and Sacrifice', 'Both passages emphasize God''s self-sufficiency and ownership of all creation. Acts 17:25 states that God ''giveth to all life, and breath, and all things,'' while Psalms 50:12 declares, ''the world is mine, and the fulness thereof.'' This connection highlights the idea that God does not require human offerings.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 25, 1, 2, 7, 7, NULL, 'Connection of Life and Breath', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''breath'' as essential for life. Acts 17:25 states that God gives life and breath, while Genesis 2:7 describes God breathing into man to give him life.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 25, 23, 42, 5, 5, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Breath', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role in giving breath and life to creation. Acts 17:25 states that God gives life and breath, while Isaiah 42:5 specifically mentions God giving breath to the people.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 25, 18, 33, 4, 4, 'breath, and all things', 'Connection of Life and Breath', 'Both passages emphasize the role of God in giving life. Acts 17:25 states that God gives ''life, and breath, and all things,'' while Job 33:4 highlights that ''the breath of the Almighty hath given me life.''', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 25, 44, 17, 28, 28, 'he giveth to all life', 'Connection of Life and Being', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of life and existence as derived from God. The idea that ''he giveth to all life'' in the source verse connects to ''in him we live'' in the target passage.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 25, 45, 11, 35, 35, 'he giveth to all life, and breath, and all things', 'Divine Self-Sufficiency Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s self-sufficiency. Both passages emphasize that God does not need anything from humanity, as He gives life and all things.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 25, 18, 22, 2, 2, 'he needed any thing', 'God''s Self-Sufficiency and Human Profitability', 'This connection highlights the idea that God does not need anything from humans, as He gives life and all things. Both passages emphasize the futility of thinking that human actions can profit God, suggesting His self-sufficiency.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 26, 5, 32, 7, 8, 'the bounds of their habitation', 'Divine Division of Nations', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role in determining the boundaries and inheritance of nations. Acts 17:26 speaks of all nations made from one blood, while Deuteronomy 32:8 describes the separation of nations and setting their bounds.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 26, 1, 3, 20, 20, 'one blood all nations of men', 'Unity of Humanity in Creation', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of a common origin for all people. Acts 17:26 refers to ''one blood'' for all nations, while Genesis 3:20 identifies Eve as ''the mother of all living.''', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 26, 39, 2, 10, 10, NULL, 'Unity of Humanity in Creation', 'Both passages emphasize the shared origin of humanity, highlighting that all nations are created from ''one blood'' and have ''one father.'' This connection underscores the importance of unity and mutual respect among people.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 26, 45, 5, 12, 19, 'one blood', 'Unity of Humanity and Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''one man'' as pivotal in the human experience. Acts 17:26 speaks to the unity of all nations from one blood, while Romans 5:12-19 discusses how sin entered through one man, Adam, affecting all humanity.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 26, 46, 15, 22, 22, 'one blood', 'Unity of Humanity in Christ', 'This connection highlights the concept of ''one blood'' in Acts 17:26, which emphasizes the shared humanity of all people. Similarly, 1 Corinthians 15:22 speaks to the universal impact of Adam''s sin and Christ''s redemption on all humanity.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 26, 46, 15, 47, 47, 'one blood', 'Connection of Humanity and Origins', 'This connection highlights the shared humanity in ''one blood'' and the distinction between the earthly and heavenly origins of humanity. Acts 17:26 emphasizes the unity of all nations, while 1 Corinthians 15:47 contrasts the first man with the second man from heaven.', 'theme', 0.377, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 26, 18, 14, 5, 5, NULL, 'Divine Determination of Boundaries', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine determination in both passages. Acts 17:26 speaks of God determining the bounds of nations, while Job 14:5 emphasizes that God has appointed bounds for individuals.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
