(44, 17, 27, 5, 4, 7, 7, 'though he be not far from every one of us', 'Proximity of God to Humanity', 'Both passages emphasize the nearness of God to His people. Acts 17:27 speaks of God being ''not far from every one of us,'' while Deuteronomy 4:7 highlights how God is ''so nigh unto them.''', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 27, 44, 14, 17, 17, 'that they should seek the Lord', 'Divine Presence and Goodness', 'Both passages emphasize God''s nearness and goodness. Acts 17:27 speaks of seeking the Lord, while Acts 14:17 highlights God''s witness through good deeds and provision.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
